Package: salso
Type: Package
Title: Sequentially-Allocated Latent Structure Optimization
Version: 0.1.2
Author: David B. Dahl
Maintainer: David B. Dahl <dahl@stat.byu.edu>
Description: Point estimation for partition distributions using the sequentially-allocated latent structure optimization (SALSO) algorithm to minimize Binder loss or the lower bound of the variation of information loss. Clustering uncertainty can be assessed with the confidence calculations and the associated plot.
License: MIT + file LICENSE | Apache License 2.0
Depends: R (>= 3.3.0)
SystemRequirements: Cargo (the Rust package manager)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: TRUE
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
